[White "1) Rare 2nd Moves after 1.e4 e5 2.Nf3"]
[Black "1A | Elephant Gambit 2...d5 | 3...Qxd5"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d5
{ The Queen's Pawn Countergambit, sometimes called the elephant gambit. Also not a particularly good choice for Black, but still with some pitfalls. At least in blitz chess it has found some strong supporters. }
3. exd5 Qxd5
{ Not a particularly challenging move, White gets a tempo with Nc3 and can develop quickly, while Black loses a lot of time with the queen. }
4. Nc3 Qc5 5. d4
{ Black has achieved nothing and White has a solid development advantage. White's moves are easy to play, Black has to be careful as White always has a few more pieces in play and is the first to set up threats. After  5...exd4  , both  6.Qxd4  and  6.Nxd4  are possible. }
