c6 7. dxc6 { Of course we continue to capture and keep the pawn. } 7... bxc6 8.
Ba4 O-O 9. O-O c5
{ Black tries to take the support away from our knight on e5. However, we can still ignore the threat because after ...cxd4 Qxd4 the knight would be protected again. }
10. Nc3 Qe7 11. Nc4
{ White saves the knight and Black is forced to seek their fortune in an incorrect sacrifice... }
11... Bxh2+ 12. Kxh2 cxd4 13. Bf4
{ White gives back the piece and goes for quick development. The bishop covers potential mating attacks with ...Ng4 and ...Qh4.   13.Qxd4?  ­− only not because of  13...Rd8  and the queen can no longer find a safe place. }
13... Ng4+ 14. Kg1 { Black wins back the piece, but White's position is huge. }
