Qe7 5. Nd4 Qe5 6. Nb5
{ A typical motive to regroup the knight to the more stable c3-square.   6.Nf3  Qe7  7.Nd4  is a repetition of a move, but of course we want to win. }
6... a6 7. d4
{ A strong intermediate move. White drives the queen away from the central e5-square and makes room for the c1-bishop. }
7... Qe7 8. N5c3
{ White is winning, Black has problems eliminating the d5-pawn and the e4-pawn is also weak.  After  8...f5  I recommend  9.Nd2  followed by f2-f3 with easy play and a winning position for White. }
