11... Bc5
{ Black gives back the knight without a fight, but hopes to gain counterplay against the weak point f2.   11...Qh4  12.Bd3!  Bc5  13.bxc3  transposes to the current variation. }
12. bxc3 Bxf2+ 13. Kxf2 Qh4+
{ Black wins back the piece, but the difficulties with the rook on f8 remain. }
14. Kf3 Qxc4 15. Bxh6
{ White inevitably wins the exchange on f8. Before that, all that remains is to escape the queen's checks. The best way to do this is for the white king to run away on the black squares so that the black c8-bishop doesn't bring itself into play with the discovered check ...d5. }
15... Qxc3+ 16. Kf4 Qd2+ 17. Kg3 Qc3+ 18. Kh4 Qc4+ 19. g4
{ And the checks come to an end. } *

