{ Simple and strong. We exchange the central knight - the only developed black piece.   4.Nxe5??  − you shouldn't react like this.  4...Qg5  5.Nxf7?  . Consistent, but wrong. After the capture on g2, Black will win more material than White or even mate.  5...Qxg2  6.Rf1  Qxe4+  . Now White must give up the queen, otherwise a nice mate will follow.  7.Be2  Nf3#  . }
4... exd4 5. O-O Nf6 6. d3 d6 7. c3
{ Battle for the center, White also prepares for ideas with Qb3 and an attack against f7. }
7... dxc3 8. Nxc3 Be7 9. d4
{ White has established a stable center, next comes Bb3 to pre-empt tactics like ... Nxe4 followed by ...d5. The immediate ... Nxe4 doesn't work }
9... Nxe4 10. Qh5 { White threatens mate and to capture the knight on e4. }
10... g6
{ Black defends the mate, but causes new weaknesses and can no longer castle. }
11. Qf3 Nf6 12. Bh6
{ Black is stuck with the king in the center and is already lost. } *

