11. Bb3 Kh8 12. f6 gxf6 13. Rxf6
{ White has compensation. Black has a weakened king position and White has various ideas to attack, e.g. Rf2 with the idea of Bg5-f6 or even Bh6.   Black has permanent problems on the dark squares and White's dark-squared bishop can prove decisive. }
