9... Qxd4 10. cxd4 Be6 11. d5
{ We avoid the exchange and fix the c7-pawn on the half-open c-file. } 11...
Bd7 12. Nc3 O-O-O 13. O-O Nf6
{ would be too passive. Black gets no counterplay while White can create weaknesses on the queenside. Finally, White can also use the half-open c-file to attack the pawn on c7. }
14. f3 Nh5 15. a4 g5 16. a5
{ White makes progress while Black threatens nothing serious } 16... Nf4 17. a6
b6 18. Bb5
{ After the exchange of the light-squared bishops the knight moves to b5. Black has problems with the pawns on a7 and c7, White can also use the weak c6-square as an outpost. }
