9. Qg5 g6 10. Nc3 f6 11. Qg3
{ Black has driven away the queen, but the weaknesses remain. } 11... b6 12.
O-O Bb7 13. Rad1 Qe7 14. h4
{ And the questions remain, where to put the black king, where should the knight go? The following variations illustrate the problems that await Black. }
14... Kf7 { 14...Rd8  15.a4⩲  , Black can barely move and is clearly worse. }
15. f4
{ White can open the position at the right moment with a decisive effect. }
15... exf4 16. Bxf4
{ White is winning, Black cannot complete the development and prevent the invasion on the black squares. White can consider ideas such as Be5 or Bg5, Bxf6 and e4-e5. }
