8... Nf6 9. Qxe5 O-O 10. Bg5
{ This prevents relieving moves like ...Qd6 and prepares Nd2 followed by O-O-O. White has an easier game and also an objective advantage. Black has problems with defending the f6-knight and developing the c8-bishop. }
10... h6 11. Bh4 b6 12. Nd2 Bb7 13. O-O-O
{ White is better due to greater activity and better attacking chances. The black h6-pawn can be used as a hook to open lines after, for example, f2-f3, g2-g4-g5.   Since the white king's position on the queenside has no weaknesses, Black is much slower with a potential counterattack. }
