11. Nxc7+ Kd8 12. Nxa8
{ The position is already won for White here, but it is worth taking a closer look at a few tactical ideas. Black has several ideas to capture the knight, but none of them work. }
12... Nge7
{ This is no better, White wins by the typical liberation of the knight. } 13.
O-O-O+ Bd7 14. Bxa7
{ There are already many ways to Rome here, White also wins, for example, by  14.Qxg6  hxg6  15.Bxa7  Nxa7  16.Nb6+-  The knight escapes and White wins back the sacrificed piece. }
14... Nxa7 15. Qxe5
{ This position might seem familiar: What we saw here is almost identical and the same conclusion applies: White wins. With queens on the board, the black king has no rest and the white attack plays itself. Moreover, the knight now escapes from the corner with ease. }
*

