{ This is strong. White can't gain an advantage here, but at least wins back the pawn with Nb5. }
9. Nb5 Kd8 10. Qh5
{ 10.Qe2  can also be examined, here White does not rely on winning back the pawn, but on long-term play against the king on d8. }
