Nge7 9. Nb5
{ Now the knight comes via b5, the c7-pawn is weak and Black has to protect it with  9...Kd8  . }
9... Kd8 10. Bg5 { This is even stronger than simply capturing on f7. } 10...
Qg6 11. Bxe7+ Nxe7 12. Qxe5
{ White got the pawn back and the initiative against the exposed black king is just getting started. }
12... d6 13. O-O-O
{ White is winning Black has big problems with king safety and White is already threatening sacrifices on d6. }
