{ After the check it becomes clear that Black doesn't have enough play for the pawn. The knight on a5 can sometimes get into trouble with Bd2. }
8... c6 { 8...Bd7  9.Bxd7+  Qxd7  10.Bd2!  and Black has big problems. } 9.
dxc6 bxc6 10. Ba4
{ White is better, Black can't drive away the f3-knight with e5-e4 and doesn't get any counterplay for the sacrificed pawn. }
