{ The main variation. Here we will surprise Black with a rare move, which is ten times rarer than the 'normal' 6 Bb5+, but still contains a few challenging ideas. }
6. d3
{ White wants to stay on c4 with the bishop. If Black captures on c4, the pawn on d5 is protected by a pawn and Black cannot get the pawn back.   If Black does not capture on c4, the knight a5 can sometimes remain offside. Of course, Black has ways to equalise the position, but accuracy is required and the surprise effect plays into White's hands. }
