{ 9.Nb3?  allows a typical idea by Black which you should have seen once, so that you will not fall for it.  9...Bg4  10.Qd2  Nxc4  11.dxc4  e3  12.fxe3  Ne4  . ...Qh4+ follows and Black wins. }
9... exd3 10. Bb5+
{ An interesting intermediate check. After  10...c6  the black knight can no longer return from a5. }
10... c6 11. Bxd3 O-O 12. O-O
{ Now Black can choose to play with or against the isolani, but White is fine either way. }
12... cxd5 13. Nd2 { White reaches an equal middlegame. } *

